scaleGen(starting_note, scale_type):
scaleGen('C', 'major') returns an object called 'scaleGen()' which is structured like so:

scaleGen().the_scale = An array containing the notes of the scale.  eg ['C','D','E','F','G','A','B']
scaleGen().root = Returns the root note of the scale.  eg 'C'
scaleGen().diatonic_triad_notes = An array containing an array containing notes for each diatonic triad.  eg ['C','E','G']
scaleGen().diatonic_triad_names = An array containing the names of each diatonic triad.  eg ['CM','Dm','Em','FM','GM','Am','Bdim']
scaleGen().pentatonic_scale = An array containing the notes of the pentatonic scale.  eg ['C','D','E','G','A']
scaleGen().relative_minor = If the scale is major this returns the starting note of the relative minor scale.  eg 'A'
scaleGen().relative_major = If the scale is minor this returns the starting note of the relative major scale.  eg 'Eb'
scaleGen().scale_type = Returns the type of scale.  eg 'major'
scaleGen().scale_intervals = Returns an array containing the intervals of the scale in half steps.  eg [2,2,1,2,2,2]

Start: Can be any note; C, D#, Eb, G, É
Scale: major, blues, natural_minor, harmonic_minor, melodic_minor

